  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And when he knew it of the centurion,.... Who might inform him of his giving up the ghost after he had cried with a loud voice, which so much affected him; and how he was found to be really dead when they came to break the legs of the malefactors; and how that one of the soldiers pierced his side with a spear, from whence flowed blood and water; so that there was no room to doubt of his being really dead; with which Pilate being satisfied, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "he gave the body to Joseph; ordered it to be given to him; gave him leave to take it down from the cross, and inter it. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "he gave the body to Joseph; ordered it to be given to him; gave him leave to take it down from the cross, and inter it. ",
